cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of understanding the structure of a real-world scene given several images of it, which is a fundamental problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also mentions wearable cameras, autonomous vehicles, and drones, which suggests that it may be relevant to robotics (cs.RO). Theoretical aspects of geometry are also discussed, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to graphics (cs.GR) as it deals with the geometry of multiple cameras.
